What is the distribution of diversity across years for the whole system?

This shows an artifact that needs to be addressed in 2008. When Multi-racial became an option it changes how the statistic is calculated and shows a large drop that year. The small decline from then on appears to be a real pattern though.

### The distribution of diversity is weighted on being very diverse. 

mean_diversity <- entropy_index %>% filter(School.year == "2015") %>% ungroup %>% summarize(mean =  mean(index))

entropy_index %>% filter(School.year == "2015") %>% ungroup %>% mutate(diff = abs(index - mean_diversity$mean)) %>% filter(diff == min(diff))
